cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and summarization. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel framework for abstractive summarization. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of transformer-based models for text generation. It could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with summarizing scientific articles. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks for text generation.
